definitions.definition: ( Chinese philosophy and religion ) Alternative letter-case form of Tao : the way of nature or way to live one's life .

main_definition: ( Chinese philosophy and religion ) Alternative letter-case form of Tao : the way of nature or way to live one's life .

definitions.definition: The art or skill of doing something in harmony with the essential nature of the thing .
examples: the tao of sex... the tao of the heart... the tao of integuments...

definitions.definition: Synonym of circuit : various administrative divisions of imperial and early Republican China .

main_definition: ( by extension ) The art or skill of doing something in harmony with the essential nature of the thing .
secondary_definitions: ( historical , obsolete ) Synonym of circuit : various administrative divisions of imperial and early Republican China .
